{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a807c939-2394-4f8e-8ff1-8e66267c992a","content":"In xUnit v3 with MTP, the `--filter` syntax changes in two ways:\n\n**1. The flag itself changes:**  \n`--filter` → `--treenode-filter` (MTP doesn't use VSTest's filter engine)\n\n**2. The expression syntax changes:**  \nVSTest's `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke` becomes a tree-node filter path with a trait filter:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**Breakdown:**\n\n| VSTest syntax | MTP tree-node filter |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*` (glob on node path) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (trait filter in brackets) |\n| `&` (AND) | Traits appended to the path pattern |\n\n**Alternative** — if you only need the trait filter and the class name match is redundant:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**Key differences to know:**\n- `~` (contains) becomes glob wildcards `*...*`\n- Traits use `[key=value]` bracket notation instead of a separate property\n- `/` separates namespace/class/method levels in the tree","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1002404d-13e5-4852-bec4-6119b60c9241","outputTokens":336,"requestId":"BD00:2CA3BD:1DAE739:2163777:6A07C58F"},"id":"a61d0fb6-8ed3-4382-ba5d-6f15c78743b8","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:17:12.502Z","parentId":"dbe6b5f0-ccff-496b-972d-414269870a18"}
